article.headline: UC Irvine 68, San Jose State 58
article.story: IRVINE, Calif. (AP) -- Darren Fells had 19 points, eight rebounds and a career-high five steals to lead UC Irvine to a 68-58 victory over San Jose State on Saturday night. Aaron Fitzgerald added 18 points and Ross Schraeder scored 15 for the Anteaters (4-3), who shot 56.3 percent from the floor and 58.3 percent from 3-point range. Alex Elam scored 14 of his season-high 19 points in the second half for the Spartans (3-4), who shot 38.2 percent in their third consecutive loss. Carlton Spencer added 11 points. Elam scored eight points and Spencer had six in a 16-4 surge that narrowed San Jose State's deficit to 52-50 with 5:07 to play. But Irvine responded with a 6-0 run that stretched the lead to 58-50. The Spartans' Matt Misko scored five points within two seconds to cut the margin to 58-55. Then Fitzgerald and Schraeder each made a 3-pointer to start a 10-0 spurt that gave the Anteaters a 68-55 lead with 57.3 seconds left.
